The paper deals with the formal verification of probabilistic programs, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of logic and verification (cs.LO). The paper also uses martingale-based techniques, which are commonly used in probability theory and stochastic processes (cs.PL). The paper presents an approach for proving expected sensitivity of probabilistic programs, which involves reasoning about the behavior of the program under different inputs and probabilistic outcomes, and this is a topic that is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with stochastic hybrid systems and stochastic gradient descent, which are topics that fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY), respectively.
